    public class DefaultEvolver<G extends Genotype<?>>
extends Evolver<G>
    A default Evolver that selects parentsProportion of the highest ranked Individuals from the Population, or each Species if applicable, and produces new members via recombination and/or cloning and mutation to replace the current members. If elitism is used, some number of members may be maintained to the next generation unchanged.

    • Method Detail

      • evolve

        public void evolve(Population<G,?> population)
        Description copied from class: Evolver
        Add Individuals to the given Population based on the current members and optionally species groupings.

        For non-swarm/colony based algorithms, implementations should do things like (taking Species into account if applicable):

        • Select some parents.
        • Generate new Genotypes from parents via the Evolver.recombiners and/or cloning and then mutate them via the Evolver.mutators or by calling Evolver.mutateGenotype(Genotype, boolean) .
        • Select some elites (most likely subset of parents).
        • Remove individuals other than elites from population with Population.removeIndividual(Individual).
        • Add the new Genotypes to the population (Population.addGenotype(Object...)).

        For swarm/colony based algorithms, implementations should do things like:

        • For each member of the population:
        • Generate an updated version of the genotype of the member via the Evolver.mutators.
        • Remove the member with Population.removeIndividual(Individual) and replace it with the updated genotype via Population.addGenotype(Object...)

        Specified by:
        evolve in class Evolver<G extends Genotype<?>>
